                    <t:note>
                        <t:date type="foundation" from="1733" to="1746">1733-1746</t:date>
                        <t:desc type="foundation">This church was founded by <t:roleName type="title">ʾǝtege</t:roleName>
                            <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS2682BerhanM">Mǝntǝwwāb</t:persName> over a period of
                                <t:date dur="P13Y">13 years</t:date>: she began the process in <t:date when="1733">1733</t:date>, dedicated the tābot in <t:date>1740</t:date>,
                            completed the building around <t:date when="1743" precision="low">1743</t:date> and completed the church's endowment sometime <t:date notBefore="1746">after 1746</t:date>.</t:desc>
                        <t:ab type="history">After its foundation by <t:roleName type="title">ʾǝtege</t:roleName>
                            <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS2682BerhanM">Mǝntǝwwāb</t:persName>, Dabra Ḍaḥay Qʷǝsqʷām became one of the
                            most important churches of Gondar. However, it was sacked by <t:roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</t:roleName>
                            <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9430Tewodros">Tewodros II</t:persName> in <t:date when="1866">1866</t:date>. He removed many of its manuscripts that
                            ended up in the <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0001BL">British Library</t:placeName>.
                            The church was sacked even further by the Mahdists in the <t:date from="1880" to="1890">1880s</t:date> and seriously damaged by air
                            strikes in <t:date when="1941">1941</t:date>. Although it was recently
                            restored, it lost its past glory.</t:ab>
                        <t:ab type="description">Dabra Ḍaḥay Qʷǝsqʷām is a church in the north-western part of
                                <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</t:placeName> and close to
                                <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC6540Entone">ʾAbbā ʾƎnṭonǝs</t:placeName>. It was
                            one of the most important churches of the town and richly endowed with
                            lands in <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC1712Bajana">Bāǧanā</t:placeName>, <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC1739Balasa">Balasā</t:placeName> and in <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC2767Ebenna">ʾƎbǝnnāt</t:placeName> that supported 260
                            clergy.</t:ab>
                    </t:note>
                </t:place>
                
